Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @aubergine{1}, then cut into roughly 2cm pieces.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks. Trim the @green beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Pop the aubergine onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

In the meantime, pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a #tight-fitting lid{}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @soy sauce{30%ml}, @chinese five spice{1%sachet}, garlic, @honey{30%g}, @sriracha sauce{15%g}, @tomato ketchup{3%tbsp} and @water for the sauce{100%ml}. Set your sticky sauce aside.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} to the pan and season with salt and pepper. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes}.

When the chicken is halfway through cooking, add the pepper chunks and green beans. Stir-fry until tender and slightly charred, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the veg is tender, pour the sticky sauce into the pan. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the roasted aubergine until coated in the sauce.

Remove from the heat, then taste and add more salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then stir through half the coriander and share between your bowls.

Top with the aubergine stir-fry, spooning over the remaining sauce from the pan.

Finish with a sprinkling of the crushed peanuts and the remaining coriander.

Enjoy!